<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">FF words are short, punchy, and packed with points. Each F tile contributes 4 points — double that and you have 8 points just from the pair, before any premium squares come into play. FF words tend to be compact (4-6 letters) and end in satisfying consonant clusters: BLUFF, CLIFF, STAFF. Master these and you have a reliable arsenal for tight boards.</p>

